# bernson.info Project Standards

## Architecture
- Static Next.js 14 site (App Router, `output: 'export'`) deployed to S3 + CloudFront
- Terraform (flat layout, no nested modules) manages all AWS infrastructure
- GitHub Actions CI/CD: `terraform.yml` for infra, `deploy-site.yml` for site
- Lambda (Python 3.13) syncs LinkedIn articles daily via EventBridge

## Code Rules
- DRY: shared values in `constants.js` (frontend) or `locals`/`variables` (Terraform)
- No hardcoded secrets; secrets only in `.env`, `terraform.tfvars`, or Secrets Manager
- No unnecessary comments; no commented-out code
- No unused code, functions, or resources
- No raw inline styles; all CSS in `globals.css`
- Uniform formatting: `terraform fmt`, Next.js ESLint

## Terraform
- Flat file layout: `main.tf`, `variables.tf`, `outputs.tf`, `providers.tf`, `versions.tf`, plus resource-specific files
- All variables must have `description` and `validation` blocks
- Use community modules (`terraform-aws-modules/*`) where appropriate
- IAM policies: least-privilege, no wildcard actions
- Tag all resources via `var.tags` and provider `default_tags`

## Frontend (Next.js)
- Animations via Framer Motion (`app/components/motion/` wrappers)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- CSS custom properties for theming in `:root`
- Mobile-first responsive design (breakpoints at 900px, 600px)

## Lambda (Python)
- Use `logger.info("message: %s", var)` style (not f-strings in log calls)
- Catch specific exceptions (`ClientError`, `requests.HTTPError`)
- All HTTP requests must include `timeout`
- Constants at module top level in UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
